               <floruit notBefore="1874" notAfter="1935">He was <roleName type="title">wag šum </roleName> in the late 19th-early 20th century. 
                  He succeeded his father <persName ref="PRS9104TafariW"/> at a young age in <date>1874</date> but was removed from office in <date>1876</date>. 
                  He was reappointed two decades later, in <date>1905</date> but removed a year later due to a quarrel with the local people who lodged an appeal,
                  against him at<persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/> 's court for maladministration and harsh treatment. He was reappointed for the third time in<date>1917</date>, 
                  and continued to administer <placeName ref="LOC6135Wag"/> until the Italian invasion, in <date>1935</date>.
               </floruit>
          
               
               
